President Biden met with leaders from legacy Black Civil Rights organizations to discuss the accomplishments and ongoing efforts of the Biden-Harris Administration in advancing justice and equity for the Black community and all Americans. The topics discussed included cutting health care costs and student debt, increasing public safety, advancing effective and accountable policing, protecting women's rights, protecting voting rights, combatting hate-fueled violence, strengthening the economy, and advancing opportunity for all communities. The leaders also provided their ideas on engaging the public on civil rights and other critical issues.